1 Section 2308. A. Section 40 of Article X of the Oklahoma
2 Constitution created the Board of Directors of the Tobacco
3 Settlement Endowment Trust Fund.
4 B. The members of the Board of Directors shall receive no
5 salary for serving on the Board. All members shall receive
6 necessary travel expenses for the performance of their official
7 duties in accordance with the provisions of the State Travel
8 Reimbursement Act, provided that members of the Board of Directors
9 shall be paid necessary travel expenses pursuant to the State Travel
10 Reimbursement Act by their appointing authority until the Board of
11 Directors adopts its initial budget and monies are made available
12 for expenditures pursuant to the budget.
13 C. The terms of the Board of Directors shall be staggered as
14 provided by subsection B of Section 2 of Enrolled Senate Bill No.
15 372 of the 1st Session of the 48th Oklahoma Legislature, as amended
16 by Section 4 of Enrolled House Bill No. 1003 of the 1st Session of
17 the 48th Oklahoma Legislature serve at the pleasure of their
18 appointing authorities, not to exceed a seven-year term of office.
19 D. The Board of Directors shall annually elect a chair and any
20 other officers, provided that no member shall be elected chair for
21 more than two (2) consecutive years.
22 E. The initial meeting of the Board of Directors shall be
23 called by the Attorney General and the State Treasurer.
